  "local_port": 52828,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I delete my gmail only from one device and retain the same on other devices?",
  "response": "To remove your Gmail account from one device while keeping it on others, follow these steps based on the type of device you are using:\n\n### For Android Devices:\n1. **Open Settings** on your device.\n2. Scroll down and select **Accounts** or **Users & accounts** (the option may vary depending on your device).\n3. Find and tap on **Google**.\n4. Select the Gmail account you want to remove.\n5. Tap on the **Remove account** option.\n6. Confirm the action when prompted.\n\nThis will remove the Gmail account from your Android device without affecting it on other devices.\n\n### For iOS Devices (iPhone/iPad):\n1. **Open the Gmail app** or go into **Settings** on your device.\n2. If using the Gmail app:\n   - Tap on your **profile picture** in the top right corner.\n   - Tap on **Manage accounts**.\n   - Select the account you want to remove and then choose **Remove from this device**.\n3. If using the Settings:\n   - Open **Settings**.\n   - Scroll down and select **Mail** > **Accounts**.\n   - Choose the Google account you wish to remove.\n   - Tap on **Delete Account** and confirm.\n\n### For Windows or Mac Computers:\n- If you are using a web browser:\n  1. Simply sign out of your account by clicking on your profile picture in the upper right corner of Gmail and selecting **Sign out**.\n  2. If you want to remove the account from the browser, go to the Google account page, click on your profile picture, and select **Sign out of all accounts** (or sign out of a specific account).\n\n- If you want to delete the email application (like Outlook) that\u2019s linked to your Gmail account, you can uninstall or remove the account from that application without affecting it on other devices.\n\n### Important Note:\nRemoving your Gmail account from a device does not delete your emails or account; it simply removes access to it from that specific device. Emails and account settings will remain intact on other devices.",
